  "prompt": "What aspect of studying at Oxford has surprised you the most?",
  "response": "Studying at Oxford has been an incredibly enriching experience, and one aspect that has surprised me the most is the depth and intensity of the tutorial system. Here are a few specific observations:\n\n1. **Personalized Learning**: The one-on-one or small-group tutorials are unlike anything I\u2019ve experienced before. The opportunity to engage deeply with a subject, receive tailored feedback, and have meaningful academic discussions with world-leading experts is both challenging and rewarding.\n\n2. **Academic Rigor**: The pace and expectations are incredibly high. You\u2019re expected to think critically, defend your ideas, and produce high-quality work consistently. It\u2019s intellectually demanding but also immensely stimulating.\n\n3. **Interdisciplinary Opportunities**: Despite its traditional reputation, Oxford encourages interdisciplinary thinking. I\u2019ve been surprised by how many opportunities there are to explore connections between different fields, whether through lectures, seminars, or research projects.\n\n4. **The Collegiate System**: The college system fosters a strong sense of community while still being part of a larger university. It\u2019s surprising how much your college becomes a central part of your social and academic life.\n\n5. **Global Perspective**: The diversity of thought and background among students and faculty is striking. Conversations often extend beyond academic topics to global issues, offering a broader perspective on the world.\n\nOverall, the combination of tradition, intellectual challenge, and community at Oxford has been both unexpected and deeply inspiring.",
